1
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:10,879
Ruochu

2
00:01:11,239 --> 00:01:12,920
It seems we really can't just play around anymore

3
00:01:13,079 --> 00:01:14,599
We really can't just play around

4
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:15,799
We're ending up in the hospital every day

5
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,400
I have to move faster

6
00:01:17,680 --> 00:01:19,599
I'm afraid some things can't be changed

7
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,200
What do you mean?

8
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:27,000
I'm sorry

9
00:01:27,239 --> 00:01:28,280
It's been a mess these past few days

10
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,480
I haven't been able to spend proper time with you

11
00:01:33,159 --> 00:01:34,000
Brother Honghai

12
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,200
Chen Fan, Ruochu

13
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,359
Are you two okay?

14
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:38,400
Brother Honghai, why are you here?

15
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:39,599
Ruochu called me just now

16
00:01:39,599 --> 00:01:40,359
She was worried to death

17
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:41,680
I happened to be in a meeting nearby

18
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:42,760
So I borrowed a car and came over

19
00:01:43,519 --> 00:01:44,840
Why did you get into a fight?

20
00:01:45,159 --> 00:01:46,519
It's nothing, just a few bumps

21
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,640
Let's go, let's get going

22
00:01:48,719 --> 00:01:49,680
Ruochu, you get in the car first

23
00:01:55,879 --> 00:01:56,680
Let's have a chat

24
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,079
About Guo Shuai...

25
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:07,120
Don't take it too hard

26
00:02:07,359 --> 00:02:08,159
Everything will be fine

27
00:02:11,560 --> 00:02:12,759
I blame myself for not watching over him

28
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,080
I underestimated things

29
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:15,560
It's not a big deal

30
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,000
You guys are still young

31
00:02:17,199 --> 00:02:18,080
There will be plenty of opportunities in the future

32
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:23,560
Who says there's no time?

33
00:02:24,159 --> 00:02:25,599
We have to do this Airsoft business

34
00:02:25,719 --> 00:02:27,159
You also need to get this antivirus software going

35
00:02:30,639 --> 00:02:31,199
Brother Honghai

36
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,159
Is there any potential in the tech company idea?

37
00:02:34,360 --> 00:02:35,000
Do you want to join us?

38
00:02:36,639 --> 00:02:37,080
Why?

39
00:02:37,479 --> 00:02:39,039
Is the internet cafe business bad lately?

40
00:02:41,719 --> 00:02:43,039
Relying solely on internet cafes won't work

41
00:02:43,319 --> 00:02:44,639
Guo Shuai's incident made me realize

42
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:46,599
My current strength is far from enough

43
00:02:47,039 --> 00:02:48,360
I can't even protect the people around me

44
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:50,960
It just so happens I have a buddy in my dorm

45
00:02:51,080 --> 00:02:52,159
He is a programming genius

46
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,879
We're planning to partner up on something

47
00:02:54,039 --> 00:02:54,840
He provides the technology

48
00:02:55,080 --> 00:02:55,879
I set the direction

49
00:02:56,599 --> 00:02:57,960
You mean Liang Shichu?

50
00:02:58,719 --> 00:02:59,520
You know him?

51
00:03:00,319 --> 00:03:01,719
That kid is not simple

52
00:03:01,879 --> 00:03:04,080
Two days ago, I went to Longshi Group for an interview

53
00:03:04,120 --> 00:03:05,599
A buddy of mine in the tech department told me

54
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:07,159
Their company is currently training a batch of

55
00:03:07,159 --> 00:03:07,840
Top-notch hackers

56
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:09,319
And Liang Shichu is among them

57
00:03:10,479 --> 00:03:11,439
I feel quite guilty

58
00:03:12,639 --> 00:03:14,240
I wanted to apologize to you several times

59
00:03:14,719 --> 00:03:18,000
But I really didn't know how to bring it up

60
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:19,879
It's all in the past

61
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,080
A prodigal's return is worth more than gold

62
00:03:22,879 --> 00:03:23,919
He has already confessed to me

63
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,680
Is that really a confession?

64
00:03:25,879 --> 00:03:27,280
He just knows you're soft-hearted

65
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,439
And is trying to win your sympathy

66
00:03:28,759 --> 00:03:30,039
You can't trust what a hacker says

67
00:03:30,479 --> 00:03:32,120
If he could do that for money back then

68
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,680
He could also do it now for your resources

69
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,039
And temporarily hide his claws

70
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:37,240
Everyone makes mistakes sometimes

71
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,439
Give him a chance, and give ourselves a chance

72
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:41,439
I've been looking at the antivirus software he made recently

73
00:03:41,639 --> 00:03:42,520
It's very clean

74
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:43,800
No...

75
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:46,080
Chen Fan, I know you cherish talent

76
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:46,719
But I think

77
00:03:46,719 --> 00:03:47,639
You shouldn't easily forgive

78
00:03:47,639 --> 00:03:48,800
Someone who has hurt you in the past

79
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,680
Be careful that he might...

80
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:50,520
If you employ someone, don't suspect them

81
00:03:50,879 --> 00:03:51,680
I trust him

82
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:52,800
Besides

83
00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:54,400
He didn't hide anything at all

84
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:56,719
Daring to admit it makes him better than many people

85
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:58,520
No, Chen Fan...

86
00:03:58,520 --> 00:03:59,319
Enough, Brother

87
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:00,639
I'll take you to meet him in a bit

88
00:04:00,719 --> 00:04:02,400
You'll understand once you meet him

89
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:03,719
Let's go

90
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:19,600
I can't convince you,

91
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,720
but Brother Liang's code definitely can.

92
00:04:22,079 --> 00:04:23,800
Chen Fan, who is this?

93
00:04:24,160 --> 00:04:25,000
This is Brother Honghai.

94
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,000
A friend from my hometown.

95
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:27,000
Hello, Brother Honghai.

96
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:27,399
By the way,

97
00:04:27,399 --> 00:04:28,680
the antivirus software

98
00:04:28,680 --> 00:04:29,639
you showed me at the hotpot restaurant that day,

99
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:30,680
show it to Brother Honghai.

100
00:04:30,680 --> 00:04:31,199
Okay.

101
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:33,759
Come here.

102
00:04:35,439 --> 00:04:37,680
Brother Liang is optimizing the core code right now.

103
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,160
See for yourself if his skills are solid enough.

104
00:04:44,199 --> 00:04:45,680
You even know this encryption algorithm?

105
00:04:47,279 --> 00:04:48,399
Brother Honghai understands this too?

106
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:51,319
I wanted to wait until it was optimized to test it.

107
00:04:52,079 --> 00:04:53,800
I didn't expect you to spot it.

108
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,600
I wasn't bragging, was I?

109
00:04:55,720 --> 00:04:56,600
With Brother Liang's skills,

110
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,839
he'd be top-tier anywhere.

111
00:04:57,879 --> 00:05:00,399
Our internet company needs this kind of foundation.

112
00:05:01,079 --> 00:05:02,040
The tech is alright.

113
00:05:02,079 --> 00:05:03,000
But as for the person...

114
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,360
Come on, Brother Honghai.

115
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:06,480
The DomainNet matter,

116
00:05:06,480 --> 00:05:07,720
is in the past as of today.

117
00:05:07,879 --> 00:05:10,079
None of us three should mention it again.

118
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,319
So Brother Honghai knows about that too.

119
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,079
But don't worry.

120
00:05:14,439 --> 00:05:15,600
Chen Fan trusts me,

121
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:16,839
and I won't let him down.

122
00:05:17,040 --> 00:05:18,920
I will definitely use my skills for the right path.

123
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:20,639
Don't give me that empty talk.

124
00:05:20,639 --> 00:05:21,639
Wait until your code runs

125
00:05:21,639 --> 00:05:22,600
without bugs, then we'll talk.

126
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,480
That's the spirit.

127
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:25,600
You understand the market,

128
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,399
I understand the direction,

129
00:05:26,399 --> 00:05:27,839
and Brother Liang handles the tech.

130
00:05:27,879 --> 00:05:29,959
The three of us have to make something of this.

131
00:05:30,879 --> 00:05:31,720
By the way, Brother Liang,

132
00:05:32,079 --> 00:05:33,600
once the company is set up,

133
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,120
I'll give you thirty percent of the shares.

134
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:36,639
Don't talk about things so far off yet.

135
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:37,800
I told you before,

136
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:39,480
I want to test the waters in a few internet cafes.

137
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:40,480
I changed this part.

138
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,399
Can you take a look for me?

139
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:42,360
Right here.

140
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:42,920
Changed it.

141
00:05:43,519 --> 00:05:44,040
This one.

142
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:46,279
The library has to be built on the local server.

143
00:05:47,120 --> 00:05:48,839
We can't let them succeed.

144
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,160
If they succeed,

145
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:51,399
then I'm useless.

146
00:05:52,160 --> 00:05:53,120
To avoid data leaks.

147
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:55,079
Right, that's why I put it here.

148
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:55,959
This part of yours,

149
00:05:56,399 --> 00:05:58,000
the compatibility with the internet cafe system is too poor.

150
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,319
Connecting it rashly is risky.

151
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,439
I already thought of that.

152
00:06:00,439 --> 00:06:02,279
So I added an optimization patch.

153
00:06:03,639 --> 00:06:04,879
Thorough.

154
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,000
Open it and let me see.

155
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:06,439
Okay.

156
00:06:12,079 --> 00:06:12,920
Brother Fan

157
00:06:13,319 --> 00:06:14,839
Found a reliable construction team

158
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:15,879
Found them

159
00:06:17,279 --> 00:06:19,319
Just change the carousel area to a sniper hideout

160
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:20,399
Make sure to keep a distance from the original facilities

161
00:06:20,399 --> 00:06:21,759
and maintain a thirty-centimeter buffer

162
00:06:23,439 --> 00:06:25,079
The floor here in the bumper car area is sanding

163
00:06:25,079 --> 00:06:26,879
Should we redo it with self-leveling cement

164
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,120
Yes, do it

165
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,680
Uneven ground is a tripping hazard

166
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:31,279
Oh, right

167
00:06:31,959 --> 00:06:33,279
All these right-angle covers

168
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:35,639
need three centimeters of EVA cushioning foam

169
00:06:35,639 --> 00:06:36,319
to prevent bumps

170
00:06:36,319 --> 00:06:37,279
What foam? What foam?

171
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,920
It's fine, the master worker knows

172
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:41,319
Alright, I've got all the details

173
00:06:41,439 --> 00:06:42,360
I didn't expect President Chen

174
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,920
looking like such a young student

175
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,800
to be so savvy about construction sites

176
00:06:46,439 --> 00:06:47,680
Thanks for your hard work these past few days, guys

177
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,079
I'll treat the brothers to a better meal tonight

178
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,000
Oh, you're too kind, too kind

179
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:52,000
At our current speed

180
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:54,439
we'll definitely be able to start trial operations by month's end

181
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:55,439
Don't worry, no problem

182
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,439
The next one is here

183
00:07:00,439 --> 00:07:00,800
Come on

184
00:07:01,079 --> 00:07:01,800
Thanks for the hard work, brothers

185
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:03,319
Thank you, thank you

186
00:07:03,319 --> 00:07:03,839
Thank you, boss. Thank you

187
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:04,879
The blueprints are drawn clearly

188
00:07:04,879 --> 00:07:06,279
It makes our work effortless

189
00:07:06,279 --> 00:07:06,839
Right?

190
00:07:07,199 --> 00:07:07,839
Boss Chen

191
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:08,720
It's already dark

192
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,720
It's twelve o'clock

193
00:07:09,839 --> 00:07:10,680
Aren't you going back yet?

194
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,040
Oh, right

195
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,120
It is twelve

196
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:14,879
I'll head back first then

197
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:15,720
You guys take care

198
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,160
No problem, no problem

199
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:16,720
Thanks for the hard work

200
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:17,279
Take care

201
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:27,399
It's always hard to get a car at this time

202
00:07:29,319 --> 00:07:31,319
Maybe I should rent a place off-campus

203
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,600
Yeah

204
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:35,879
Ruochu

205
00:07:36,839 --> 00:07:37,279
You're back

206
00:07:37,279 --> 00:07:38,560
I bought you roasted corn from the school gate

207
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:39,680
Smells so good

208
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:40,240
Smells good, right?

209
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:40,839
It's hot, don't burn yourself

210
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:41,920
Why are your hands so hot?

211
00:07:42,040 --> 00:07:42,560
Just out of the oven

212
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,439
Don't touch it

213
00:07:44,480 --> 00:07:44,920
Blow out the candles

214
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:49,519
Happy Birthday

215
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:53,160
Where was that house again?

216
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:55,759
Mr. Chen

217
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,279
You say you're not short on money

218
00:07:57,519 --> 00:07:59,040
There are plenty of good houses out there

219
00:07:59,319 --> 00:08:00,920
Why do you insist on unit 505?

220
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,519
Look at this faculty apartment building

221
00:08:03,519 --> 00:08:04,680
It's old and the layout is poor

222
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,839
And besides

223
00:08:06,079 --> 00:08:06,839
Besides what?

224
00:08:07,399 --> 00:08:09,360
And the owner of unit 505 you specified

225
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,439
has a somewhat special situation

226
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,920
If renting, she won't rent the whole unit

227
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,480
You have to share it with the owner

228
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:15,519
If buying, it's not available immediately

229
00:08:15,519 --> 00:08:17,360
Who knows how long until handover

230
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,439
Why is that?

231
00:08:18,439 --> 00:08:19,480
Money isn't a problem

232
00:08:20,199 --> 00:08:21,439
It really isn't a problem of money

233
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,399
How about I take you up to have a look?

234
00:08:28,839 --> 00:08:30,800
Miss Wen, Mr. Chen is here

235
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:33,720
You're back

236
00:08:47,039 --> 00:08:47,799
Come in, let's talk.

237
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,720
Hello, I'm Chen Fan.

238
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:55,919
Hello, my name is Wen Wan.

239
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:59,000
Do you want to rent or buy this house?

240
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,679
I want to buy.

241
00:09:00,559 --> 00:09:02,679
I can't sell this house for the time being.

242
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,360
Then I'll rent it long-term.

243
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:06,919
If you rent, you can't rent the whole place yet.

244
00:09:06,919 --> 00:09:08,399
I still need to live here for a while.

245
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,919
But don't worry.

246
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:12,600
On weekdays, I have to stay at the hospital with my mom.

247
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:13,639
I only come back occasionally.

248
00:09:13,639 --> 00:09:14,720
I won't be here all the time.

249
00:09:15,600 --> 00:09:18,120
In a few days, I might have to go on a long trip.

250
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:21,919
That... that works too.

251
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:23,919
Take a look at the property deed.

252
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:25,519
Look.

253
00:09:29,320 --> 00:09:31,279
Why are these medical records all in English?

254
00:09:34,200 --> 00:09:37,879
My mom has a rare disease.

255
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:39,919
It's rarely seen in the country.

256
00:09:40,519 --> 00:09:41,639
The doctor said...

257
00:09:42,279 --> 00:09:43,919
...only one professor abroad...

258
00:09:44,080 --> 00:09:46,440
...has implemented a relatively mature treatment plan.

259
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,480
But I've used all my connections...

260
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,279
...and still can't find his contact information.

261
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,279
Indeed.

262
00:09:53,879 --> 00:09:55,879
People in this era aren't familiar with the internet.

263
00:09:56,679 --> 00:09:58,639
But I can help her.

264
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:02,720
So I urgently need the rent money.

265
00:10:03,039 --> 00:10:05,320
I want to buy a plane ticket abroad in a couple of days.

266
00:10:05,519 --> 00:10:07,600
To go straight to his medical school and catch him.

267
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:09,519
Don't fly there.

268
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,639
You might not find him even if you go.

269
00:10:12,600 --> 00:10:14,240
I can try to help you contact him.

270
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:14,960
You?

271
00:10:16,039 --> 00:10:16,799
How will you contact him?

272
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:18,759
I'm from the Computer Science Department at Yunhai University.

273
00:10:18,759 --> 00:10:19,440
A student.

274
00:10:19,799 --> 00:10:21,840
I know a little bit about the internet.

275
00:10:22,039 --> 00:10:24,320
You can organize the details of your mom's condition first.

276
00:10:24,519 --> 00:10:26,320
I'll try to send a plea letter to the professor.

277
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,919
If he sees it...

278
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,000
...doctors are benevolent...

279
00:10:29,000 --> 00:10:30,039
...I believe he won't ignore it.

280
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,679
As for the rent...

281
00:10:31,679 --> 00:10:33,039
I can pay for a year...

282
00:10:33,039 --> 00:10:34,039
...to you today.

283
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:36,120
If I can't find him...

284
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:38,440
...it won't be too late to use this money for the ticket.

285
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,080
Thank you, thank you so much.

286
00:10:43,639 --> 00:10:44,559
You really are a good person.

287
00:10:44,799 --> 00:10:45,639
A great person.

288
00:10:45,639 --> 00:10:47,080
No, no, don't be so polite.

289
00:10:55,080 --> 00:10:55,840
Chen Fan.

290
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,840
I'm staying up late updating the antivirus software database.

291
00:10:58,919 --> 00:10:59,919
What are you busy with now?

292
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,159
Trying to help a friend contact...

293
00:11:01,159 --> 00:11:02,720
...a foreign professor specializing in rare diseases.

294
00:11:03,039 --> 00:11:04,440
But this guy is too low-key.

295
00:11:04,639 --> 00:11:05,519
I've tried all kinds of methods.

296
00:11:05,519 --> 00:11:07,039
I can't find any public information on him.

297
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:09,200
I'm trying to write emails to the...

298
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,320
...journal editorial office that published his papers...

299
00:11:10,480 --> 00:11:11,480
...and other professors...

300
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:12,919
...who have collaborated with him on projects.

301
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:15,200
Hoping they can forward it.

302
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:16,639
Darn it.

303
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:18,279
Your brain is so sharp.

304
00:11:18,279 --> 00:11:19,279
You even thought of that.

305
00:11:19,759 --> 00:11:20,279
Great.

306
00:11:20,679 --> 00:11:21,919
The dial-up connection dropped again.

307
00:11:23,399 --> 00:11:25,240
The internet in the year 2000 is torture.

308
00:11:25,440 --> 00:11:26,639
It's such a struggle just to find someone.

309
00:11:27,120 --> 00:11:28,679
Use my campus network dedicated line.

310
00:11:29,039 --> 00:11:29,879
Although it's slow...

311
00:11:30,279 --> 00:11:33,200
...the outbound speed is much faster than yours.

312
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,080
Hey, it's done.

313
00:11:35,639 --> 00:11:37,120
For your friend to know you...

314
00:11:37,120 --> 00:11:38,120
...is really just too lucky.

315
00:11:44,759 --> 00:11:46,200
This slope is really long.

316
00:11:48,720 --> 00:11:49,559
Chen Fan.
